<title>LATVIA: CENTRAL BANK TO STOP QUOTING T-BILL RATES.</title>
<headline>CENTRAL BANK TO STOP QUOTING T-BILL RATES.</headline>
<dateline>RIGA 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The central bank said on Tuesday that from April 21 it would no longer quote prices and rates for government Treasury bills in the secondary market.</p>
<p>The bank said in a statement that it would no longer quote prices as it wanted to improve the price setting mechanism in the secondary market of T-bills.</p>
<p>The bank said this would also allow it to more efficiently carry out its monetary policy.</p>
<p>-- Riga Newsroom, +371 721 5240</p>
